  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.23-stable\r\nOS & Version: OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\ngeth node syncs to mainnet\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nOriginally fast synced with pre 1.8.23 , with raised file descriptor limits to get around a \"too many open files\" error, using the command `sudo launchctl limit maxfiles 1000000 1000000`.\r\n\r\nI installed 1.8.23 a few days ago, and geth syncing always resulted in \r\n\r\n    BAD BLOCK\r\n    Number: 7260000\r\n    Hash: 0xb4f9639ba930069b84efc6149fbe84315f8b5bf2d12de3efa541bb21e9de3af7\r\n    Error: invalid mix digest\r\n\r\nI executed 'removedb' and restarted a fast synced. This kept failing. I have now executed `sudo launchctl limit maxfiles 1000000 1000000` and the syncing is progressing as expected.\r\n\r\nOther error messages when the chaindata got corrupted in the past:\r\n\r\n    INFO [02-25|16:59:43.097] Block synchronisation started\r\n    WARN [02-25|17:00:16.767] Rolled back headers                      count=160 header=7259455->7259455 fast=0->0 block=0->0\r\n    WARN [02-25|17:00:16.769] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=31e5e7c0ae800d8f err=\"retrieved hash chain is invalid\"\r\n    WARN [02-25|17:00:17.365] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=e0f7a02a46d7c52a err=\"action from bad peer ignored\"\r\n    WARN [02-25|17:00:43.594] Rolled back headers                      count=160 header=7259455->7259455 fast=0->0 block=0->0\r\n    WARN [02-25|17:00:43.594] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=31e5e7c0ae800d8f err=\"retrieved hash chain is invalid\"\r\n    WARN [02-25|17:00:54.654] Rolled back headers                      count=160 header=7259455->7259455 fast=0->0 block=0->0\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nFast sync on OS/X without raising the file descriptor limit",
