    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This ticket is a bit old -- we have reworked the file descriptor handling quite a bit since, and there were some additional quirks regarding OSX filesystem that we have navigated around. Please file a new ticket if the error persists. \r\n\r\nTo clarify: if geth believes there are more file descriptors available than the OS actually supports, the chaindata _will_ become corrupt, because leveldb will be unable to flush data to disk. So that is expected. \r\n\r\nSo the root cause was a mismatch between what geth thought was available and what was actually available, and that has been fixed. ",
